==English==

===Etymology===
{{la}} [[ad#Latin|ad]] ("next to") + ''-ject-'', perfect passive participle of ''[[jacere]]'' ("to throw") + ''-ivus'', adjective ending; hence, a word "thrown next to" a noun, modifying it.

===Noun===
'''adjective''' (''plural:'' [[adjectives]])

#{{grammar}}: A word that [[modify|modifies]] or [[describe]]s a noun or pronoun, such as ''big'' or ''heavy''.

